topic.title: Generic Features for PHY RX and PHY TX

body.p: The PHY blocks provide the PCS/FEC interfaces for:

li.p: A mix of the above inks up to a maximum of 24 links and up to 600 Gbps.

body.p: The PHY blocks generic features are listed below.

li.p: Provides BIP transparency for 100G GMP mapping/de-mapping datapaths.

body.p: It is possible to disable the PCS layer with the g5_api_enet_phy_en_set() API. This function enables or disabled the physical PCS of the Ethernet channel. It accepts three input parameters and does not return any outputs. The device_id is the device instance. The chnl_id parameter is the channel ID representing the ENET segment which will be configured. The phy_enable parameter is a boolean parameter which indicates whether the PCS layer is enabled or disabled by setting it to TRUE or FALSE respectively. The PCS layer is automatically enabled during ENET provisioning. This API is intended for debugging purposes. See the ENET Runtime Operations section for more information.
